This section describes the specific configuration of the Doxee Platform required to deliver a Pweb.

> Tip

Pweb projects can be started from scratch or added as an extension to an already existing Doxee solution.

> Important

Pre-existing knowledge of Doxee Platform services and their configuration is taken for granted.

## Required offering Items
A Pweb Solution requires the following offering items:

- **DOCCM **to create Pwebs&nbsp;

- **Digital Archiving**&nbsp;to store &amp; serve Pwebs

- **Tracking &amp; Reporting**&nbsp;to monitor Pwebs

## Configuration steps
### 1 - Data Transformation
#### The unique ID
The need for a unique key depends on the pURL type:

- In case of a **directpURL**, a unique key must be generated and set in the Output Schema for DT Configuration purposes.

- In case of an **indirectpURL**,&nbsp;a unique key is not needed.

This key will be used in the production chain to create the pURL, which must have the following syntax:

`pURL= https://{hostName]/da-purl/document/{UniqueID}`

where&nbsp;*hostName* is selected by the Client or Partner to leverage AWS CloudFront and needs to be decided before starting any development.

> Note

For more information on pURL see: [Personalized URL Delivery](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Personalized+URL+Delivery).

#### Adding a GUID attribute to the output schema
The output schema must have a string attribute, usually named ***guid***, where DT can store the unique ID.

#### Generating the GUID value
The GUID is generated by a special Common operator,&nbsp;[**GUIDGenerator**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-guidgenerator-operator), which allows to generate a unique ID regardless of the input.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

This step is not needed in case of an **indirect pURL.**

> Warning

If the GUID is not created using the **GUIDGenerator **operator, as it may occur in some situations where the GUID is generated outside DT, make sure that its length is exactly 32 characters.

Using fewer or more characters will lead to errors in DA.

#### The DT output
The DT output must follow this schema:

**DT XML Output Schema**

`&lt;FILE&gt;

			&lt;CLIENT_DATA&gt;
			&lt;/CLIENT_DATA&gt;
		&lt;/TEMPLATE&gt;
	&lt;/DOCUMENT&gt;
&lt;/FILE&gt;`An example of a DT output is shown below:

> Important

Digital Archiving does not need any particular settings for Pweb, besides having at least a Document Class and an Index.

### 3 - Document Composition
Configuring Document Composition for Pweb involves:

- editing index and pURL attributes

- editing spool set settings

- correctly creating the pURL address in the communication's body

- adding a TTS attribute in Contract file

- uploading the video template

### Editing the index and pURL attributes (Output Management)
This configuration is performed in the&nbsp;Document Composition&nbsp;**Output**&nbsp;tab.

By accessing an index in the** Files and Metadata** folder, select the dedicated tab **Digital Archiving &amp; pURL Provider**.

This mask is split in two main areas:

- the top section deals with the Digital Archiving index configuration

- the bottom sections deals with pURL configuration

#### Digital Archiving Configuration file
The Pweb-specific configuration for this file is only related to the **ShipmentID**: this field, although not mandatory for solutions without pURL, is actually mandatory for Pweb and must be set.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Warning

The mandatory * symbol is not currently displayed on the interface. Remember to set this parameter to a shipment identifier.

[DCOM-39](https://code.doxee.com/browse/DCOM-39) TODO

#### pURL generation attributes
For more information on how to generate pURL attributes, see:&nbsp;[Personalized URL Delivery](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Personalized+URL+Delivery).

### Editing Spool Set Settings (Output Management)
In this tab, there are two Pweb specific configurations that must be set:

- Creating a new file for every Pweb

- Naming Pweb files in a unique way

![](data:image/png;base64,)

#### Creating a new file for every Pweb
In order to create a new file for every Pweb, the** Break the file** option must be set to "**Every Document**".

#### Naming files in a unique and standardized way
The** Spool file Name **must be set to a unique name.

> Tip

Although there is no mandatory syntax for the name, it is a common practice to set the name to an attribute generated by string concatenation of several terms, including the ***guid***.

### pURL creation in the Communication Body
> Warning

Regardless of where the Direct pURL will appear in the communication body, it must be constructed using the syntax: ** pURL= https://{hostName]/da-purl/document/{UniqueID} **

### Loading the Pweb template (Content)
The template file provided by the authors of the video as a ZIP file must be uploaded in the&nbsp;Document Composition&nbsp;**Content**&nbsp;tab. To do so:

- Flag a document raw and select **More actions... &gt;&nbsp;Load a Pweb/Pvideo...**&nbsp;from the menu.&nbsp;The following popup will appear:![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the&nbsp;**Pweb&nbsp;**radio button.

- Click&nbsp;**Browse...** to select the ZIP archive&nbsp;(or standalone HTML&nbsp;file) containing the Pweb template from your filesystem.

- Set the **Master document name** to the name of the main HTML page which must be communicated by the video developer.

> Note

If you request a **Preview**, the system will generate a ZIP archive containing the following files:

- an HTML page for every final user (the one in which the JSON will be injected)

- a set of common files and directory

- the index file for DA

### 4 - Batch Production
The following is an example Batch Production application, containing all the tasks to run an application that produces and sends Pweb to email or SMS using direct pURL.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The input is delivered to Doxee by a SMTP server.

An Inbound Watcher SMTP rule is attached to run the application when a specific file is delivered. The input has a specific name and is in CSV format.

#### DTEmail
The DT task (**DTEmail**) takes the CSV input as the BOM&nbsp;and creates an XML file which is enriched with the GUID generated by the&nbsp;**GUIDGenerator**&nbsp;operator.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

This is its configuration:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

#### DCEmail
The DC task (**DCEmail**) takes this XML file as an input:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

It outputs two XML files:&nbsp;

- an XML file for the DA loader index containing the information about the pURL

- a *lotxml*&nbsp;file containing the information about the emails to send

Beside these XML files, the DC task will also produce the Pwebs, one for each end user.

This is the Task configuration:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

#### PackDA
The first Packaging Task (**PackDA**), takes what is needed by the DA loader task:

- the *LOADER.DA.INDEX.XML* file

- the HTML pages

- a ZIP file containing the video

> Note

For more information on the PackDa configuration, see: [Personalized URL Delivery](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Personalized+URL+Delivery).

#### DA Loader
The DA loader task (**DAEmail**) , takes the *LOADER.DA.INDEX.XML*&nbsp;file as input.

> Note

For more information on the PackDa configuration, see: [Personalized URL Delivery](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Personalized+URL+Delivery).

#### PackEmail
The second Packaging Task (**PackEmail**) takes the DC task output as input:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

and packages the files needed to pack the emails from a *lotxml.*

This is the Task configuration:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

#### Delivery
The Delivery Task (**DeliveryEmail**) takes the packaged *lotxml* and uses its data to send emails to end users.

### 5 - Tracking &amp; Reporting
A Pweb application may take advantage of the new event **Personalized URL Download**, which is generated when the user clicks on a pURL (be it in an email, a SMS text or on the Client Portal).

This event is of "**User Response"**&nbsp;type.

> Important

This event is generated by DA.

DA creates a new ZIP package of text files containing such events every hour and saves it in a folder.

> Warning

An Inbound Watcher must be configured to load it into a very simple application which uncompresses the package and passes it to a TR Loader.

In order to manage this event, the monitoring lines have to be extended with the stage "**User Response**" and the task "**Personalized Url Download**".

The triplet to be used is the following:

Item

Value

**Delivery Product**

Can be one of the following:

- Email

- SMS

- Web

**Media Format**

Pweb

**Distribution Channel**

Can be one the following:

- DXE_DXE
